// Signing.xcconfig — the ONE place the signing team lives (project.pbxproj carries none).
//
// The committed default is the SHIPPING team (Jesai's paid Apple Developer account —
// Developer ID + notarization for the release DMG require it; free accounts can't do either).
//
// Per-developer override (e.g. Aditya's free account): create `Signing.local.xcconfig` next to
// this file — it's git-ignored — containing one line:
//     DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = <your team id>
//
// ⚠️ Never pick a Team via Xcode's Signing & Capabilities dropdown: that writes an explicit
// DEVELOPMENT_TEAM back into project.pbxproj, which OVERRIDES this file and restarts the
// two-devs-two-teams pbxproj ping-pong this setup exists to kill. If a PR diff ever shows a
// DEVELOPMENT_TEAM line in project.pbxproj, that's what happened — reject it.

DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = YJ8AZR3G5Q

#include? "Signing.local.xcconfig"
